JAKARTA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian police's anti-terror squad arrested on Tuesday a suspected terrorist identified as T in Banten province's Tangerang district. "We arrested him at dawn this morning at his house," the Indonesian Police's spokesman Ahmad Ramadhan told reporters, adding that the suspect worked as a civil servant for a regional government office. Ramadhan said to date 14 suspected terrorists who were civil servants had been detained by the police. The spokesman said the suspect was affiliated with the Islamic State-linked terrorist group Jamaah Islamiyah (JI). "We are still investigating his role and involvement in JI," Ramadhan said.  â– 